main event: A round, moving object about the size of a nickel was seen to travel west at a low rate of speed for seven to eight minutes.
interesting points: The object crossed a major portion of the sky during the observation period.
The sighting occurred approximately 50 minutes after a Northwest Airlines flight from Minneapolis to Fargo, suggesting the object may have been an aircraft.
The report mentions circular, irregular objects being observed on July 6, 1955, with some being eight times nine in size and affected by the ground sight, but they could not be identified.
The circular objects were observed at various speeds, ranging from 10 knots to 500 knots, and at different altitudes.
The report suggests the objects may not be easily identifiable in this case.
